 noun","usage":"falling(2x)"},"H1763":{"id":"H1763","lemma":"דְּחַל","translit":"dᵉchal","pron":"deh-khal'","derivation":"(Aramaic) corresponding to H2119 (זָחַל);","strongs_def":"to slink, i.e. (by implication) to fear, or (causatively) be formidable","kjv_def":"make afraid, dreadful, fear, terrible.","pos":"verb","usage":"fear(2x), dreadful(2x), terrible(1x), afraid(1x)"},"H1764":{"id":"H1764","lemma":"דֹּחַן","translit":"dôchan","pron":"do'-khan","derivation":"of uncertain derivation;","strongs_def":"millet","kjv_def":"millet.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"millet(1x)"},"H1765":{"id":"H1765","lemma":"דָּחַף","translit":"dâchaph","pron":"daw-khaf'","derivation":"a primitive root;","strongs_def":"to urge, i.e. hasten","kjv_def":"(be) haste(-ned), pressed on.","pos":"verb","usage":"hasten(3x), pressed(1x)"},"H1766":{"id":"H1766","lemma":"דָּחַק","translit":"dâchaq","pron":"daw-khak'","derivation":"a primitive root;","strongs_def":"to press, i.e. oppress","kjv_def":"thrust, vex.","pos":"verb","usage":"thrust(1x), vex(1x)"},"H1767":{"id":"H1767","lemma":"דַּי","translit":"day","pron":"dahee","derivation":"of uncertain derivation;","strongs_def":"enough (as noun or adverb), used chiefly with preposition in phrases","kjv_def":"able, according to, after (ability), among, as (oft as), (more than) enough, from, in, since, (much as is) sufficient(-ly), too much, very, when.","pos":"preposition, substantive","usage":"enough(6x), sufficient(5x), from(5x), when(3x), since(3x), able(3x)"},"H1768":{"id":"H1768","lemma":"דִּי","translit":"dîy","pron":"dee","derivation":"(Aramaic) apparently for H1668 (דָּא);","strongs_def":"that, used as relative conjunction, and especially (with a preposition) in adverbial phrases; also as preposition of","kjv_def":"[idiom] as, but, for(-asmuch [phrase]), [phrase] now, of, seeing, than, that, therefore, until, [phrase] what (-soever), when, which, whom, whose.","pos":"conjunction, relative pronoun"},"H1769":{"id":"H1769","lemma":"דִּיבוֹן","tr